data.text:
Quote History

Originally Posted By DDiggler:

About what part? We've been talking for months... she just got a promotion a month ago, she was excited and showed me the email she got as well as the official letter. I know where she lives, where she works, and we talk a LOT.

How do you know that someone from the US dating sites are telling you the truth? You just have to pay attention always and look for any inconsistencies... the liars and scammers always expose themselves in time.

Also... she's insisting on taking care of my hotel reservations in Singapore and insists on paying for that and wants to split the cost of the rest of it.

You can't live in constant negativity and fear all the time. Just go into the situations with your eyes open.

Originally Posted By DDiggler:

Originally Posted By _LandCruiser_:

Originally Posted By DDiggler:

It really depends... the woman I'm meeting makes more than most in the US. Of course Singapore isn't exactly a third world country, it's actually first world, and more expensive cost of living than most of the US.

The thing to realize is that you have a LOT of choices, it's not like men's experiences in dating in the US, so take your time and be extremely picky. I've talked to dozens and dozens of women for over a year and a half before meeting one that I had an interest in meeting.

How do you know what they're telling you is the truth?

About what part? We've been talking for months... she just got a promotion a month ago, she was excited and showed me the email she got as well as the official letter. I know where she lives, where she works, and we talk a LOT.

How do you know that someone from the US dating sites are telling you the truth? You just have to pay attention always and look for any inconsistencies... the liars and scammers always expose themselves in time.

Also... she's insisting on taking care of my hotel reservations in Singapore and insists on paying for that and wants to split the cost of the rest of it.

You can't live in constant negativity and fear all the time. Just go into the situations with your eyes open.

Well said. Good advice.
